    <h3>Smart Investments </h3>

    <p>
    More meaningful analytics have also helped Carolyn make smarter investments. For example, in 2015, the data showed that the sales population lagged in participation. After deploying targeted outreach strategies, like in-person meetings, participation increased by 45%. The team was able to build a bridge to a key part of the workforce that would have otherwise been missed.
    </p>

    <h3>Engaging Employees in Many Topics and Resources</h3>

    <p>
    Today, Fujifilm and its Towers Watson consultants use Airbo as a central place from which to drive engagement in a wide variety of initiatives, from wellness to health care reform. In addition to providing a platform to create original content, Airbo is used to drive use of free vendor resources that are often underutilized. For example, Fujifilm linked a Tile to a financial education podcast from Fidelity, and asked employees a question about the content.
    </p>

    <p>
    Carolyn and her team regularly collect and analyze employee feedback about their efforts. By the end of the 3rd quarter of 2015, 84% of eligible Fujifilm employees have joined Airbo. And, more than 65% of employees who have joined log in monthly. That’s a level of engagement that drives serious results.
    </p>

    <p>
    Employee response continues to be overwhelmingly positive. In surveys, employees write the kind of statements that look like paid testimonials: “What a great incentive to motivate employees, it’s fun and healthy!!” said one employee. “I feel like Fujifilm really cares about us.” That’s a big change from just a few years ago.
    </p>

